<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[188,1408,1153,1549]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Notes. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Angel" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[281,546,1153,1181]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microlepis">
<emphasis box="[281,546,1153,1181]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Mesalina microlepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schenkel" authorityYear="1901" box="[1012,1183,1153,1181]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bernoullii">
<emphasis box="[1012,1183,1153,1181]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. bernoullii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, contrary to what Angel (1936) suggested it cannot be distinguished from it by the numbers of dorsal and gular scales, and subdigital lamellae. The only morphological character that discriminates the species is the structure of the lower eyelid window. All specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Angel" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[1081,1259,1263,1291]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microlepis">
<emphasis box="[1081,1259,1263,1291]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. microlepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(including the 
<typeStatus box="[237,351,1300,1328]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">holotype</typeStatus>
) possess a window consisting of more than three roughly equal semitransparent scales whereas the window of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schenkel" authorityYear="1901" box="[593,764,1337,1365]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bernoullii">
<emphasis box="[593,764,1337,1365]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. bernoullii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer, 2017" authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" box="[783,986,1337,1365]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="brevirostris" status="s. s.">
<emphasis box="[783,986,1337,1365]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. brevirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[989,1042,1337,1365]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" sensu="stricto">s. s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the new Saudi species consists of 1–3 larger semitransparent scales (see Fig. 
<quantity box="[932,987,1373,1401]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
Mayer 
<emphasis box="[1099,1161,1374,1402]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2006). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Angel" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microlepis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1407,1374,1402]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Mesalina</taxonomicName>
microlepis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schenkel" authorityYear="1901" box="[398,582,1410,1438]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bernoullii">
<emphasis box="[398,582,1410,1438]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<collectionCodeEnum box="[398,429,1410,1438]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M</collectionCodeEnum>
. bernoullii
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been confirmed to occur syntopically in western 
<collectingCountry box="[1332,1408,1410,1438]" name="Syria" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Syria</collectingCountry>
(Mayer 
<emphasis box="[292,357,1447,1475]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
2006). The presence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Angel" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[677,865,1447,1475]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microlepis">
<emphasis box="[677,865,1447,1475]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<collectionCodeEnum box="[677,708,1447,1475]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M</collectionCodeEnum>
. microlepis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[901,986,1447,1475]" name="Jordan" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Jordan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1052,1144,1447,1475]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Turkey</collectingCountry>
is confirmed based on specimens with similar eyelid window structure (Haas &amp; Werner 1969; Kumlutaş 
<emphasis box="[1332,1399,1484,1512]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al.</emphasis>
2002).
</paragraph>
